

       
      Microsoft pays Lindows.com $20M to end trademark fight
 
WASHINGTON (CBS.MW) -- Lindows.com said Microsoft (MSFT) will pay $20 million to settle a trademark dispute between the companies, according to a Monday regulatory filing. Under the settlement, Microsoft will buy the rights to the Lindows.com domain name along with other related sites. Microsoft sued the company in 2001 claiming the company infringed on Microsoft's trademark patents for its Windows operating system. Shares gained 28 cents to $27.76 in morning trading. "
       
    
